                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2003-11-10</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Painter's biography is excellent.  She puts Truth in perspective with the  challenges of her time.  She sheds light on complicated relationships with noteable Abolishionists and with her own children.  This book clearly presents the difficult life of one incredible woman who struggles to do her part to free all slaves, gain respect as a woman and be accepted as a human being.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">SOJOURNER TRUTH A LIFE A SYMBOL</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>0</span>
                      /
                      <span>3</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
